<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7441592>
    dc:description "FIGURE 67. Ovaticoccus gordoni sp. n., adult female, Big Bend National Park, 2.3 miles N. of Main Rd., on Point Gap Rd., Brewster Co., Texas, USA, May 26, 1976, on Viguiera stenoloba, D.R. Miller and R.D. Gordon.A=enlarged seta (not present on this specimen); B=slightly enlarged seta; C=7-locular pore; D=5-locular pore; F=microtubular duct; H=cruciform pore; I=anal ring; J=antenna; L=claw; W=leg; Z=body margin (hatched areas on the body of the inset with dermal projections)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7441592/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

